The paper deals with visual recognition systems and utilizes knowledge graphs to make predictions for images belonging to previously unknown class labels. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a learning framework with smoothness constraints and incorporates prior knowledge into the model, indicating that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Finally, the paper proposes a new dataset, which suggests that it may also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
